Dr. Jerry F. Miller, Research Geneticist (Adjunct Professor, Dept. of Plant Sciences, NDSU) millerjf@fargo.ars.usda.gov; (701) 239-1321
Research involves morphological and biometrical genetic studies of sunflower with emphasis on the inheritance of factors leading to improvements in yield, oil quality, plant morphology and disease and insect resistance.
The research program is involved with germplasm enhancement, developing lines with specific characteristics having high combining ability for yield and oil, resistance or tolerance to pests, desired quality characteristics, and adaptation to north central U.S. environments.
